night-madness-2013 |last=Darney |first=Caroline |website=Streaking the Lawn |date=30 October 2013 |accessdate=8 August 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n===Incoming transfers===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\"\n! Name !! Number !! Pos. !! Height !! Weight !! Year !! Hometown !! class=\"unsortable\" | Previous School\n|-\n|sortname| [[Darius Thompson]] || 51 || G || 6'5\" || 181 || Sophomore || [[Murfreesboro, Tennessee|Murfreesboro,&nbsp;TN]] || Transferred from [[Tennessee Volunteers basketball|Tennessee]].<ref name=\"thompson\">{{cite web |title=Darius Thompson Joins Virginia Men's Basketball Program |url=http://www.virginiasports.com/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/053014aaa.html |website=VirginiaSports.com - The University of Virginia Official Athletic Site |date=30 May 2014 |accessdate=8 August 2014}}</ref> Under NCAA transfer rules, Thompson must redshirt for the 2014\u201315 season. After this season he will have three years of remaining eligibility.\n|}\n\n==Class of 2014 signees==\n{{College Athlete Recruit Start|40=no|collapse=no|year=2014}}\n{{College Athlete Recruit Entry\n| recruit = [[Jack Salt]]\n| position = C\n| hometown = Auckland, New Zealand\n| highschool = Westlake High School\n| feet = 6\n| inches = 10\n| weight = 230\n| 40 = \n| commitdate = 09/18/2013<ref name=\"salt\">{{cite web | title = Jack Salt, 6-10 Center from New Zealand, Commits to Virginia | url = http://www.streakingthelawn.com/2013/9/18/4744232/jack-salt-new-zealand-uva-basketball-recruiting-2014 | first = Brian | last = Schwartz | website = Streaking The Lawn | date = 18 September 2013 | accessdate = 8 August 2014}}</ref>\n| scout stars = NR\n| rivals stars = NR\n| 247 stars = 3\n| espn stars = NR\n}}\n{{College Athlete Recruit Entry\n| recruit = [[Marial Shayok]]\n| position = SG\n| hometown = Ottawa, Ontario\n| highschool = Blair Academy\n| feet = 6\n| inches = 6\n| weight = 205\n| 40 = \n| commitdate = 04/22/2014<ref name=\"shayok\">{{cite web | title = Virginia Cavaliers Basketball Recruiting: Shayok Commits! | url = http://www.streakingthelawn.com/2014/4/22/5642070/virginia-cavaliers-basketball-recruiting-marial-shayok-tony-bennett | first = Matt | last = Trogdon | website = Streaking The Lawn | date = 22 April 2014 | accessdate = 8 August 2014}}</ref>\n| scout stars = 3\n| rivals stars = 3\n| 247 stars = 3\n| espn stars = 3\n}}\n{{College Athlete Recruit Entry\n| recruit = [[B. J. Stith]]\n| position = SG\n| hometown = Brunswick, Virginia\n| highschool = Oak Hill Academy\n| feet = 6\n| inches = 5\n| weight = 200\n| 40 = \n| commitdate = 09/03/2011<ref name=\"stith\">{{cite web | title = B.J. Stith | url = http://virginia.sportswar.com/player/B.J.-Stith-3343/ | website = TheSabre.com | accessdate = 8 August 2014}}</ref> \n| scout stars = 3\n| rivals stars = 3\n| 247 stars = 4\n| espn stars = 3\n}}\n{{College Athlete Recruit Entry\n| recruit = [[Isaiah Wilkins]]\n| position = SF\n| hometown = Norcross, Georgia\n| highschool = Greater Atlanta Christian School\n| feet = 6\n| inches = 8\n| weight = 210\n| 40 = \n| commitdate = 09/01/2013<ref name=\"wilkins\">{{cite web | title = New Virginia Basketball Commitment: SF Isaiah Wilkins | url = http://www.streakingthelawn.com/2013/9/2/4687604/new-virginia-basketball-committment-sf-isaiah-wilkins | first = Paul |last = Guttman | website = Streaking The Lawn | date = 2 September 2013 | accessdate = 8 August 2014}}</ref>\n| scout stars = 3\n| rivals stars = 4\n| 247 stars = 3\n| espn stars = 3\n}}\n{{College Athlete Recruit End\n| 40               = \n| year             = 2014\n| rivals ref title = Virginia Basketball Commitment List\n| scout ref title  = 2014 Virginia Basketball Commitment List\n| espn ref title   = ESPN\n| rivals school    = virginia\n| scout s          = \n| espn schoolid    = \n| scout overall    = \n| rivals overall   = \n| espn overall     = \n| accessdate       = \n| bball            = yes}}\n\n== Roster ==\nOn November 7, 2014, head coach Tony Bennett announced, via a Virginia athletic department press release, that London Perrantes and Evan Nolte would be suspended for two scrimmages and the first game of the season due to a violation of team rules.<ref name=\"en_lp_suspended\">{{cite web |url=http://www.virginiasports.com/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/110714aaa.html |title=Nolte and Perrantes Suspended For Season-Opener and Scrimmages |work=VirginiaSports.com - The University of Virginia Official Athletic Site |date=7 November 2014 |accessdate=7 November 2014}}</ref> Following the first game of the season against James Madison, Bennett stated that Jack Salt was \"leaning\" towards a redshirt, but he had not made a final decision yet.<ref name=\"JMU_pressconf\">{{cite web |title=MEN'S BASKETBALL: Tony Bennett Post James Madison |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7QoZ7N_ljaA |date=14 November 2014 |accessdate=17 November 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn February 7, 2015, Justin Anderson suffered a broken finger in his left hand during the Louisville game.<ref name=\"anderson_injury\">{{cite web |url=http://www.virginiasports.com/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/020715aaa.html |title= Justin Anderson Out 4-6 Weeks With Fractured Finger |website=VirginiaSports.com |date=7 February 2015 |accessdate=7 February 2015}}</ref> He had surgery the next day, and was expected to return to playing after four to six weeks,<ref name=\"anderson_surgery\">{{cite web |url=http://www.virginiasports.com/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/021015aab.html |title= Anderson Moves Into Supporting Role |first=Jeff |last=White |website=VirginiaSports.com |date=February 10, 2015 |accessdate=February 11, 2015}}</ref> but an emergency appendectomy on March 5 kept him sidelined.<ref name=\"appendectomy\">{{cite press release |url=http://onlyfans.cstv.com/schools/va/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/030515aaa.html |title=Anderson Out Saturday Following Appendectomy |publisher=[[Virginia Cavaliers|University of Virginia Sports]] |date=March 5, 2015 |accessdate=March 9, 2015}}</ref> Anderson returned to play seven days later, against Florida State in the ACC Tournament quarterfinals.<ref name=\"FSU_0312_postgame\">{{cite press release |title= ACC Tournament Postgame Notes: #1 Seed Virginia vs. #9 Seed Florida State |url=http://www.virginiasports.com/sports/m-baskbl/recaps/031215aae.html |publisher=[[Virginia Cavaliers|University of Virginia Sports]] |date=March 12, 2015 |accessdate=March 15, 2015}}</ref>\n{{multiple image\n<!-- Essential parameters -->\n| align     = right\n| direction = vertical\n| width     = 160\n\n| image1    = Malcolm Brogdon 2014.jpg\n| width1    = \n| alt1      = \n| caption1  =\n\n| image2    = Anthony Gill.jpg\n| width2    =\n| alt2      = \n| caption2  =\n\n| image3    = Darion Atkins.jpg\n| width3    =\n| alt3      = \n| caption3  =\n\n| header            = \n| header_align      = <!-- left/right/center -->\n| header_background = \n| footer            = Redshirt juniors [[Malcolm Brogdon]] (top) and [[Anthony Gill (basketball)|Anthony Gill]] (middle) served as tri-captains with senior [[Darion Atkins]] (bottom) for the 2014\u201315 campaign.\n| footer_align      = <!-- left/right/center -->\n| footer_background = \n| background color  = \n}}\n{{CBB roster/Header|year=2014|team=Virginia Cavaliers|teamcolors=y|high_school=yes}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Devon|last=Hall|num=0|pos=G|ft=6|in=5|lbs=203|class=FR|rs=yes|home=[[Virginia Beach, Virginia]]|high_school=[[Cape Henry Collegiate School|Cape Henry Collegiate]]|link=y}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Justin|last=Anderson|dab=basketball|link=y|num=1|pos=G|ft=6|in=6|lbs=228|class=JR|home=[[Montross, Virginia]]|high_school=[[Montrose Christian School|Montrose Christian]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=B. J.|last=Stith|link=y|num=2|pos=G|ft=6|in=5|lbs=205|class=FR|home=[[Lawrenceville, Virginia]]|high_school=[[Oak Hill Academy (Mouth of Wilson, Virginia)|Oak Hill Academy]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Marial|last=Shayok|link=y|num=4|pos=G|ft=6|in=5|lbs=207|class=FR|home=[[Ottawa|Ottawa, Ontario]]|high_scho