 estimate)<ref>Struve (1993) (note at p. 269), following a 1964 article by Zhang Defang, notes that the entire city's population at the time was not likely to be more than 300,000, and that of the entire Yangzhou Prefecture, 800,000.</ref>\n|\n|-\n|[[Dzungar genocide]]\n|1755\u20131757\n|[[Dzungar Khanate]]\n|{{ntsh|540000}}540,000<ref>Geometric mean of 480 and 600 thousand rounded up to nearest ten thousand.</ref>\n|480,000 to 600,000 deaths. 80% of population killed {{citation needed|date=November 2016}}\n|-\n|[[Ningpo Massacre]]\n|1800s\n|[[Ningbo]]\n|{{ntsh|40}}40\n|Cantonese pirates supported by the Qing massacred 40 Portuguese pirates.\n|-\n|[[Jindandao incident]]\n|1891\n|[[Inner Mongolia]]\n|{{ntsh|150,000}}150,000 - 500,000\n|Ethnic tensions led a Chinese secret society, Jindandao, to revolt and kill 150,000 - 500,000 Mongols.\n|-\n|[[Port Arthur massacre (China)|Port Arthur massacre]]\n|1894, November 21\n|[[L\u00fcshunkou]], [[Liaoning]]\n|{{ntsh|4500}}4500\n|1000\u201320,000{{citation needed|date=February 2017}}\n|-\n|[[Kucheng Massacre]]\n|1895, August 1\n|[[Gutian County|Gutian]], [[Fujian]]\n|{{ntsh|11}}11\n|11 British Missionaries killed by a fasting folk religious group on August 1, 1895\n|-\n|[[Taiyuan Massacre]]\n|1900, July\n|[[Taiyuan]], [[Shanxi]]\n|{{ntsh|45}} 45\n|\n|}\n\n== Republic of China (1912\u20131949) ==\n\n=== 1912\u20131937 ===\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" \n!Name\n!Date\n!Location\n!Deaths\n!Notes\n|-\n|[[Shanghai massacre of 1927]]\n|1927, April 12\n|[[Shanghai]]\n|{{ntsh|1200}}1200\n|300\u2013400 direct deaths. 5000 missing\n|-\n|[[Anti-communist mass killings#China|Kuomintang Anti-Communist massacre]]\n|1928\n|Nationwide in [[China]]\n|{{ntsh|300000}}300,000<ref name=\"Barnouin38\">Barnouin, Barbara and Yu Changgen. ''Zhou Enlai: A Political Life.'' Hong Kong: Chinese University of Hong Kong, 2006. {{ISBN|962-996-280-2}}.  Retrieved at <https://books.google.com/books?id=NztlWQeXf2IC&printsec=frontcover&dq=zhou+enlai&hl=en&ei